# Documentation maintenance

Whenever you **implement or materially change** behavior (features, routes, validation, edge functions, DB schema/migrations, env vars, integrations, or user-visible flows), **update documentation in the same change**, not as a follow-up the user must request.

## What to update

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| Architecture, routes, env vars, API surface, data model, flows, deployment | **`docs/PROJECT.md`** — adjust the relevant section(s); add new tables/rows if you add endpoints or columns |
| Shipped / cancelled backlog items, new roadmap tasks | **`docs/TODOS.md`** — checkboxes, wording, or new bullets so backlog matches reality |
| Anything about the **new booking flow redesign** (status machine, admin dashboard, Gmail listener, SD refund cron, new emails) | **`docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md`** — update the plan as decisions land, answered questions, and phases ship. Also flip items to answered / in progress / done |
| Database migration or one-shot backfill instructions | **`docs/MIGRATION_RUNBOOK.md`** (create when Phase 0 lands) |
| Global conventions agents rely on (paths, stack, “where things live”) | **`.cursor/rules/project-context.mdc`** if the old text would mislead future sessions |
| New Edge Function patterns or JWT/CORS policy | **`.cursor/rules/supabase-edge-functions.mdc`** if the shared contract changed |
| Booking status / transition / side-effect matrix changes | **`.cursor/rules/booking-workflow.mdc`** — this file is canonical |
| Admin auth rules, allow list, or new admin endpoints | **`.cursor/rules/admin-auth.mdc`** |

## Rules of thumb

- Prefer **small, accurate edits** over rewriting the whole doc unless the feature is cross-cutting.
- If you add a **new query param, env var, or HTTP route**, document it in `docs/PROJECT.md` (API tables or env sections).
- If behavior **diverges** from what `docs/PROJECT.md` says, **fix the doc**—do not leave contradictions.
- Do **not** create extra markdown files unless the user asked for them; stay within `docs/` and `.cursor/rules/` for this project.

## When docs need no change

Trivial fixes (typos, formatting, rename of internal variable with no API/UX impact) do not require doc updates unless they touch documented names.
